        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> I am ok with your review though Chenfei, the timestamp\n > serialization, if needed could be worked out at a later time.\n\nI see your point. You are saying I should change to use Instant as the type instead of String, right? I can change that easily but using custom parser is tricky since we also need to configure the data binding in JAX-RS. What if I change it to Instant but don't provide the custom parser?",
